data.title: The Bridge to Anacostia is Not Built Yet. But Here’s What We Could Learn.
data.meta_description: A decade in the works, the 11th Street Bridge Park in Washington, D.C., has yet to be built. But it could be a model for how to create public space while lessening the effects of gentrification.
data.text:
Megan Kimble is the former executive editor at the Texas Observer. She is writing a book about highways, forthcoming from Crown. @ megankimble

Andre D. Wagner is a photographer based in Brooklyn, New York. His work investigates the American social landscape through the lens of race, class, cultural identity and community. He is a 2022 recipient of a Gordon Parks Foundation Fellowship.

​​Produced by Jason Chiu, Leo Dominguez, Eve Lyons, Vera Titunik, and Rumsey Taylor.
